data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in EF Core 11 that opt-in no longer exists. All four of your methods will **throw at runtime** — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()`.

### Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This means callers must also become `async`/`await` up the chain. There is no workaround — the Cosmos SDK is async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.

**Also relevant to your Cosmos DB setup:** empty owned collections now return an empty collection instead of `null`, so update any `is null` checks to `.Count == 0`.
